To us?

501
00:49:18,055 --> 00:49:19,579
Yes.

502
00:49:19,656 --> 00:49:21,647
You're the unknown angel?

503
00:49:21,725 --> 00:49:22,749
Yes.

504
00:49:22,826 --> 00:49:25,659
The one you're looking for.

505
00:49:25,729 --> 00:49:26,661
Optimistic.

506
00:49:26,730 --> 00:49:28,789
He is unknown.

507
00:49:28,865 --> 00:49:29,797
The angel part's

508
00:49:29,866 --> 00:49:31,128
questionable.

509
00:49:31,201 --> 00:49:32,828
Very.

510
00:49:42,512 --> 00:49:44,503
How romantic.

511
00:49:44,581 --> 00:49:46,879
There's a novel about you, too.

512
00:49:54,291 --> 00:49:57,658
I started to collect these.

513
00:50:03,333 --> 00:50:07,497
This is the first one I grew.

514
00:50:07,571 --> 00:50:09,129
Now I'm not saying
that this boat

515
00:50:09,206 --> 00:50:10,935
you have built isn't worthy.

516
00:50:11,041 --> 00:50:12,406
From the looks of it,

517
00:50:12,476 --> 00:50:14,808
you've done a mighty fine job.

518
00:50:14,878 --> 00:50:18,075
But for the sake of my job,
let's just say

519
00:50:18,148 --> 00:50:20,082
it doesn't.

520
00:50:20,150 --> 00:50:22,311
Doesn't what?

521
00:50:22,386 --> 00:50:24,479
Your boat doesn't float.

522
00:50:24,554 --> 00:50:25,953
Imagine this, if you will.

523
00:50:26,056 --> 00:50:27,387
One day,

524
00:50:27,457 --> 00:50:30,221
a town on the plains,
let's say Northfork,

525
00:50:30,293 --> 00:50:32,727
was hit by a catastrophic flood,

526
00:50:32,796 --> 00:50:35,128
similar to
the days of Noah,

527
00:50:35,198 --> 00:50:36,529
and you husband
and yourselves

528
00:50:36,600 --> 00:50:39,228
are standing out there on
the roof waiting to be rescued.

529
00:50:39,302 --> 00:50:40,394
A friendly neighbor

530
00:50:40,470 --> 00:50:43,598
comes paddling by in
his little wooden boat,

531
00:50:43,673 --> 00:50:45,504
and he yells, "Hey, there,
Mr. and Mrs. Stalling,

532
00:50:45,575 --> 00:50:47,065
"and... uh, Mrs. Stalling,

533
00:50:47,144 --> 00:50:49,374
jump on in
and I'll take you to dry land."

534
00:50:51,181 --> 00:50:52,705
What do you say?

535
00:50:52,783 --> 00:50:54,410
I don't know.

536
00:50:54,484 --> 00:50:55,508
The water's rising.

537
00:50:55,585 --> 00:50:56,677
You shout back,

538
00:50:56,753 --> 00:50:58,414
"No, thank you,
thy friendly neighbor.

539
00:50:58,488 --> 00:51:01,946
I'm waiting
for a sign from God."

540
00:51:02,025 --> 00:51:02,923
No, thank you.

541
00:51:03,060 --> 00:51:06,518
I'm waiting for a sign from God.

542
00:51:06,596 --> 00:51:07,563
Yes, exactly.

543
00:51:07,631 --> 00:51:10,099
And your friendly neighbor
paddles away.

544
00:51:13,303 --> 00:51:15,237
A few days later

545
00:51:15,305 --> 00:51:19,264
a state rescue team
comes by in a larger boat.

546
00:51:19,342 --> 00:51:21,572
And let's just say

547
00:51:21,645 --> 00:51:24,944
me and Willis are on board.

548
00:51:25,048 --> 00:51:28,313
And we offer you the same deal.

549
00:51:28,385 --> 00:51:30,114
"Jump on in,

550
00:51:30,187 --> 00:51:34,624
"and you, Mrs. Stalling
and... Mrs. Stalling,

551
00:51:34,691 --> 00:51:36,420
will be saved."

552
00:51:36,493 --> 00:51:41,055
And you say...

553
00:51:41,131 --> 00:51:42,689
No, thank you.

554
00:51:42,766 --> 00:51:46,099
We're waiting
for a sign from God.

555
00:51:46,169 --> 00:51:49,263
A few more days pass,

556
00:51:49,339 --> 00:51:52,831
and the water level has risen.

557
00:51:52,909 --> 00:51:56,140
