01:32:25,805 --> 01:32:29,741
1.5 acres
of lakefront property.

1114
01:32:29,809 --> 01:32:30,969
Hmm.

1115
01:32:31,043 --> 01:32:33,409
Northern Pike?

1116
01:32:33,479 --> 01:32:34,810
Might be.

1117
01:32:34,881 --> 01:32:36,542
Pike's not a fish.

1118
01:32:36,616 --> 01:32:38,140
It's a dog.

1119
01:32:38,217 --> 01:32:40,481
Skull full of teeth.

1120
01:32:40,553 --> 01:32:42,783
Pick those suckers up
by their eye sockets.

1121
01:32:42,855 --> 01:32:45,483
Weapons of massive destruction.

1122
01:32:45,558 --> 01:32:46,547
They drop that

1123
01:32:46,626 --> 01:32:48,389
pike's milt into this lake.

1124
01:32:48,461 --> 01:32:50,122
You can forget
all about the fish

1125
01:32:50,196 --> 01:32:51,993
living in peace and harmony.

1126
01:32:52,064 --> 01:32:55,295
Pike eat their children.

1127
01:32:55,368 --> 01:32:57,393
What they should do
is introduce a nice game fish

1128
01:32:57,470 --> 01:32:58,664
like the Muskie.

1129
01:32:58,738 --> 01:33:00,501
Now, that's a fine species.

1130
01:33:00,573 --> 01:33:01,699
- Mm.
- No fish

1131
01:33:01,774 --> 01:33:03,435
from Minnesota
should be allowed to swim

1132
01:33:03,509 --> 01:33:05,443
past the Missouri.

1133
01:33:05,511 --> 01:33:07,103
The fine citizens
of Northfork knew

1134
01:33:07,180 --> 01:33:09,774
that Muskie was swimming
through their houses,

1135
01:33:09,849 --> 01:33:11,817
we would've never been able
to get'em to leave.

1136
01:33:11,884 --> 01:33:12,976
Canada ought to claim

1137
01:33:13,052 --> 01:33:16,419
that bug-heap they
call Minnesota.

1138
01:33:16,489 --> 01:33:18,957
Throw in Wisconsin for free.

1139
01:33:26,499 --> 01:33:28,729
You have to think
that this must have been

1140
01:33:28,801 --> 01:33:31,133
his last day on the job.

1141
01:34:47,813 --> 01:34:49,440
You ready?

1142
01:34:49,515 --> 01:34:52,780
1,000 miles?

1143
01:34:54,053 --> 01:34:55,850
Farther.

1144
01:34:55,955 --> 01:34:58,014
You're a relative.

1145
01:35:03,829 --> 01:35:06,195
Hercules...

1146
01:35:06,265 --> 01:35:10,793
the strongest man
ever to wear a skirt.

1147
01:35:10,870 --> 01:35:14,601
Are you going to be my mother
or my father?

1148
01:35:14,674 --> 01:35:17,302
I'm both.

1149
01:35:19,178 --> 01:35:22,341
Considered the perfect soul,

1150
01:35:22,415 --> 01:35:24,042
I search for no one,

1151
01:35:24,116 --> 01:35:25,640
and no one looks for me.

1152
01:35:25,718 --> 01:35:26,742
Whatever

1153
01:35:26,819 --> 01:35:29,117
I need I look
within myself to find.

1154
01:35:29,188 --> 01:35:30,120
I am

1155
01:35:30,189 --> 01:35:31,588
complete.

1156
01:35:31,657 --> 01:35:35,787
I am not king nor queen,
yet I am both.

1157
01:35:35,861 --> 01:35:38,659
A mother and a father.

1158
01:35:38,731 --> 01:35:41,928
You prayed to be this way?

1159
01:35:42,001 --> 01:35:44,663
Isn't that
what Father Harlan says?

1160
01:35:44,737 --> 01:35:46,432
"Pray and you shall receive?"

1161
01:36:21,474 --> 01:36:24,238
Would you like a cup of tea?

1162
01:37:22,902 --> 01:37:24,802
Irwin?

1163
01:37:26,472 --> 01:37:28,201
Well?

1164
01:37:43,489 --> 01:37:45,650
There you go, son.

1165
01:38:07,379 --> 01:38:11,110
And in that journey of dying,

1166
01:38:11,183 --> 01:38:14,084
you see many things.

1167
01:38:14,153 --> 01:38:18,180
But all issues I had passed.

1168
01:38:18,257 --> 01:38:21,749
Because I was to be a witness.

1169
01:38:21,827 --> 01:38:25,024
A helper.

1170
01:38:25,097 --> 01:38:28,464
And that's the thing, I think,

1171
01:38:28,534 --> 01:38:31,594
is important about death,

1172
01:38:31,670 --> 01:38:34,230
is the ability for us

1173
01:38:34,306 --> 01:38:36,137
to be witnesses.

1174
01:38:36,208 --> 01:38:40,304
Not only for our births
of coming in,

1175
01:38:40,379 --> 01:38:43,143
but going out.

1176
01:38:43,215 --> 01:38:46,480
And that's what we have here.

1177
01:38:46,552 --> 01:38:48,713
We've lost our town. It's gone.

1178
01:38:48,787 --> 01:38:51,779
But maybe there's

1179
01:38:51,857 --> 01:38:54,951
a birth someplace else.

1180
01:38:55,027 --> 01:38:57,325
Maybe there's a blessing

1181
01:38:57,396 --> 01:39:00,661
from that experience.

1182
01:39:00,733 --> 01:39:03,702
I'm no longer afraid of death,

1183
01:39:03,769 --> 01:39:05,862
but it's a lesson
that's taken me

1184
01:39:05,938 --> 01:39:08,372
60 years to learn.

1185
01:42:32,344 --> 01:42:34,972
As you stroll around Northfork,

1186
01:42:35,047 --> 01:42:37,948
take your last walk
down the dirt road

1187
01:42:38,016 --> 01:42:40,280
that leads to where
your house may have been,

1188
01:42:40,352 --> 01:42:44,152
and look at the trees
that you once climbed.

1189
01:42:44,223 --> 01:42:49,456
Smile, and remember those trees
for what they will become:

1190
01:42:49,528 --> 01:42:53,020
future snags
for fishing tackle.

1191
01:42:53,098 --> 01:42:56,261
As you continue your walk,
think to yourself,

1192
01:42:56,335 --> 01:43:00,795
"This is the only time
I will ever be able

1193
01:43:00,873 --> 01:43:03,569
"to walk
on the bottom of a lake

1194
01:43:03,642 --> 01:43:06,509
without having
to hold my breath."

1195
01:43:06,578 --> 01:43:09,911
Remember when you leave
to pack all your good memories.

1196
01:43:09,982 --> 01:43:13,383
No one else will pack them
for you.

1197
01:43:13,452 --> 01:43:15,079
Good night to you all.

